node.text: Every time she laces up her 1461 Bex shoes, Tokyo-based model Miu knows they are her own window into history that she can put a stamp on. “I think of the meaning, the backbone and culture of the time, and wear them with that knowledge”. Heritage built in, with plenty of room leftover for your story. From pit to stage. Every scuff and scratch. Wherever you’re going.

node.text: I- MUSE Berbershop in Shanghai is a rare moment of quiet and nostalgia in a fast-paced world. For I- MUSE founder Henry, his style choices are defined by vintage simplicity. “Just like the 1461 shoe, I coordinate with my bike. They’re the same. Made by brands that can stand the test of time.” A subcultural classic for decades. One foot in our heritage and the other on the accelerator.

German artist Gabriel Holzner (@createdbygabe) is putting self-expression front and centre. Through curating an exhibition alongside Dr. Martens Presents in an iconic Munich location, he is using five pieces of bespoke artwork created with 
members of the city’s creative community to help provide a break from social isolation and celebrate art’s ability to connect people.

node.text:
“For me, punk ideology and queerness have always gone hand in hand.” In high school, Art Director Spencer Singer saw his 1461 shoes as a symbol of the protest and rebellion that are embedded in LGBTQ+ history. As a closeted teenager, Spencer’s 1461s offered protection and a way to identify other people who shared his beliefs. More than just a shoe. A shield. And a community.

@jenny.shoo.pumps

node.text:
Nova Twins are a rock duo rebelling against the norm. Through their playlist, Voices For The Unheard, they’re also working to highlight underrepresented POC talent. Watch the interview as they are joined by special guests to talk about their music, their inspirations and what it is to be a POC in alternative music.

Featuring: @novatwinsmusic @itsconniesworld @bigjoanieband @death.tour @loatheasone

node.text: DR. MARTENS x HEAVEN BY MARC JACOBS | The Audrick 8i HMJ Croc boot and 3i shoe come with the spirit of self-expression stitched in. Stacked on a towering Quad Neoteric platform sole — an amplified and unmissable air-cushioned sole with a built-in SoftWair insole for added comfort. Lightweight and pre-welted with a tonne of attitude. Available 09.09. 8AM BST/PST/JST.

node.text:
'OUR FREEDOM IS LINKED TO THE FREEDOM OF ALL OPPRESSED PEOPLE’

Fusing her technical background with a focus on the body, Becca McCharen-Tran (she/they) creates designs for boundary-breaking women. Motivated by the impact fashion had on her own upbringing – she's shaping the fashion industry into a more inclusive and accessible space. Find out more via the link in our bio.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Dr. Martens on September 06, 2021 tagging @heavn. May be an image of boots and text that says 'มาย'.

node.text: DR. MARTENS x HEAVEN BY MARC JACOBS | Crossing paths for the first time almost 30 years ago — when Marc Jacobs sent his models charging down the runway in DM’s boots at his notorious 1993 runway show — our DIY-heavy, anti-establishment relationship started as it meant to go on. This season we’re uniting with the designer’s newest collection, Heaven by Marc Jacobs, for a celebration of 90s nostalgia, teen angst and self-expression. Lands 09.09. Sign up via the link in our bio.
